{"header":"<h1>Module <code><span>Operator.Concrete</span></code></h1>","type":"documentation","uses_katex":true,"breadcrumbs":[{"name":"Index","href":"../../../index.html","kind":"leaf-page"},{"name":"codex","href":"../../index.html","kind":"page"},{"name":"Operator","href":"../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Concrete","href":"#","kind":"module"}],"toc":[],"source_anchor":null,"preamble":"<p>Concrete interpreter using OCaml boolean and <code>Z.t</code> for values.</p>","content":"<p>The interpreter values can be:</p><ul><li><code>{true, false, empty}</code> for booleans;</li><li>any <code>Z.t</code> or <code>empty</code> for integers;</li><li>the set of bitvectors (represented by <code>Z.t</code> + empty). Empty is not an error, just a special value representing the absence of value.</li></ul><p>But, considering that whenever an argument is empty, the result is empty, we can build an interpreter by focusing on the non-empty values, and just return an exception for the (infrequent) empty cases.</p><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec exception anchored\" id=\"exception-Empty\"><a href=\"#exception-Empty\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">exception</span> </span><span><span class=\"exception\">Empty</span></span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec module anchored\" id=\"module-Types\"><a href=\"#module-Types\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">module</span> <a href=\"Types/index.html\">Types</a></span><span> : <span class=\"keyword\">sig</span> ... <span class=\"keyword\">end</span></span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec module anchored\" id=\"module-Boolean_Interp\"><a href=\"#module-Boolean_Interp\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">module</span> <a href=\"Boolean_Interp/index.html\">Boolean_Interp</a></span><span> : <span class=\"keyword\">sig</span> ... <span class=\"keyword\">end</span></span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec module anchored\" id=\"module-Bitvector_Interp\"><a href=\"#module-Bitvector_Interp\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">module</span> <a href=\"Bitvector_Interp/index.html\">Bitvector_Interp</a></span><span> : <span class=\"keyword\">sig</span> ... <span class=\"keyword\">end</span></span></code></div></div>"}